      "title": "Cambridge Analytica to cease all operations",
      "body": "Cambridge Analytica, the data firm at the centre of the Facebook privacy scandal, is shutting down.\n\nCambridge Analytica and its parent, SCL Elections, said on Wednesday they would begin bankruptcy proceedings after losing clients and facing mounting legal fees following reports the company wrongly harvested Facebook users' personal data from 2014. Pictured right: Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg yesterday.\n\n\"Despite Cambridge Analytica's unwavering confidence that its employees have acted ethically and lawfully... the siege of media coverage has driven away virtually all of the company's customers and suppliers\". In an announcement on its website, Cambridge Analytica said it and affiliated companies are immediately ceasing all operations and have filed applications to commence.\n\nCambridge Analytica released a statement announcing the closure overnight, which pointed to the continual \"vilification\" of the firm as the cause of its insolvency.\n\nAfter Facebook discovered the transaction in 2015, it demanded Cambridge Analytica delete all the information it had obtained.\n\nA sign belonging to the firm outside its London offices has already been taken down. Workers in NY were told to leave the office as soon as possible without hearing of any potential compensation. Facebook banned the UK-based political data analysis firm last month, saying it had improperly received data from as many as 87 million user profiles. The app collected data on tens of millions of people and their Facebook friends.\n\nThese records were used to target particular voters with ads and social media posts in hope of influencing their decisions at the ballot box.\n\nCambridge Analytica has been linked to Donald Trump's 2016 presidential campaign.\n\nThis information is said to have been used to help the Brexit campaign in the UK.\n\nIn light of those accusations, noted Queen's Counsel Julian Malins was retained to conduct an independent investigation into the allegations regarding the Company's political activities. GSR was only ever a contractor to Cambridge Analytica and we understand it did work for many other companies.",
