      "url": "https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/breaking-cambridge-analytica-closing-operations-12336975",
      "title": "Cambridge Analytica 'closing operations' after Facebook data scandal",
      "body": "Cambridge Analytica is closing operation after the ongoing Facebook data scandal saw it lose many of its clients, according to reports.\n\nSCL Group and its Cambridge Analytica consultancy, at the center of this year's Facebook privacy row, are closing, the Wall Street Journal reported today, quoting company managers.\n\nThe newspaper added, citing an unnamed source, that the decision was taken because the companies were losing clients and facing mounting legal fees in the Facebook investigation.\n\nThe firm did not immediately respond to a request for comment.\n\nThe row over the improper use of data on 87 million Facebook users by Cambridge Analytica in President Donald Trump's 2016 U.S. election campaign, has hurt the shares of the world's biggest social network and prompted multiple official investigations.\n\nIt is also reported to have been involved in the Leave campaign in the build up to the Brexit referendum.\n\nThe firm is shutting down effective Wednesday and employees have reportedly been told to turn in their computers.\n\nThe business had $15 million in U.S. political work in the 2016 election cycle.",
